# CelebSkin Project Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 14 with App Router (NOT Pages Router)
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS dark theme
- PostgreSQL 16 with JSONB for 10 languages
- Redis 7 for caching
- Node.js 20 LTS

## Architecture
- All text fields use JSONB: {"en": "...", "ru": "...", "de": "...", ...}
- 10 languages: en, ru, de, fr, es, pt, it, pl, nl, tr
- URL: /[locale]/video/[slug], /[locale]/celebrity/[slug], /[locale]/movie/[slug]
- Table name: "celebrities" (NOT "actresses")
- Database: celebskin, user: celebskin
- CDN: BunnyCDN at cdn.celeb.skin
- Site dir: /opt/celebskin/site
- Config: /opt/celebskin/config/.env
- Full spec: /opt/celebskin/MASTER_README.md

## Code Style
- Use "pg" library for PostgreSQL (NOT Prisma, NOT Drizzle)
- Server Components by default, "use client" only when needed
- Parameterized queries ($1, $2) — never string interpolation
- API routes under /api/
- Admin under /admin/ (no locale prefix)

## AI Models
- NEVER change AI models without explicit user request
- Gemini 2.5 Flash for content generation
- Gemini 2.5 Pro for complex tasks

## Design
- Dark theme: bg #0a0a0f, cards #12121a, hover #1a1a2e
- Accent: #e50914 (red)
- Text: #e5e5e5, secondary #888
- Font: Inter
